value.value: Objective evidence of bacterial infection perceptible to the examiner by laboratory procedure.

label.value: Blocked Atrial Premature Complex by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of premature atrial complexes which are not conducted to the ventricle, and which are not followed by a QRS complex. (CDISC)

label.value: Blocked Ventricular Premature Complex by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of a premature ventricular complex which occurs between two normal QRS complexes which have normal timing. (CDISC)
A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to cardiovascular system findings.
A way of contracting a disease through everyday interactions (nonsexual) with an infected person.
There are no signs or symptoms of disease in the individual who previously had a disease.
There are still signs or symptoms of disease in the individual who previously had an infection.

label.value: Contact With Exposure During Medical Procedure

value.value: A way of contracting a disease by interacting with an individual that has been exposed to the disease while undergoing a medical procedure.

label.value: Contact With Exposure In Crowd Setting

value.value: A way of contracting a disease by physically associating with an infected group of individuals.
A way of contracting a disease by interacting with an individual that is considered at high risk for having the disease.
System of classification based on the nation in which an individual was exposed to a disease, regardless of the nation in which he/she currently resides.

label.value: Current or Recent Employee or Volunteer in Homeless Shelter

value.value: An individual who is presently or not long ago worked or offered to assist without pay at a temporary housing facility for persons without a stable or permanent residence.

label.value: Current or Recent Employee or Volunteer in Jail or Prison

value.value: An individual who is presently or not long ago worked or offered to assist without pay at an institution where persons are confined for punishment and to protect the public.

label.value: Current or Recent Employee or Volunteer in Nursing Home

value.value: An individual who is presently or not long ago worked or offered to assist without pay at a residential health care facility for persons with chronic illness or disability.
A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to device events.
A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to device exposure.
A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to device identifiers.
A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to device properties.
A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to device to subject relationship.
A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to device tracking and disposition.
A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to device-in-use.

An electrocardiographic finding suggestive of dextrocardia with situs inversus, characterized by reversal of normal anterior R wave progression and the appearance of reversal of the right and left arm electrodes. (CDISC)
Medication is dispensed and consumed under the direct supervision of personnel at a clinical site.

A public health activity whereby individuals who have been exposed to a person with a suspected or confirmed contagious illness are identified, usually for the purpose of identifying additional cases of the illness, or to offer some form of prophylactic intervention to either prevent or ameliorate disease in the exposed individual.
The determination of whether the microbe or lesion is resistant to drugs normally used in treatment.

Venous channels within the dura mater of the brain which receives both blood from blood vessels within the brain as well as cerebrospinal fluid then drains into the internal jugular vein. Unlike other blood vessels, dural venous sinuses lack valves and other vessel associated layers.

label.value: Early R Wave Transition by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding where the amplitude of the R wave becomes greater than the amplitude of the S wave in the QRS complex at an unusually early point in the precordial leads, usually in leads V1 or V2. (CDISC)
An electrocardiographic finding of J point and ST segment elevation in the absence of other signs of acute ischemia or pericarditis. (CDISC)
A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to endocrine system findings.

label.value: Entry Date from Country of Potential Disease Exposure

value.value: The date on which the subject arrived in the reporting country from the country of potential disease exposure.

A highly sensitive immunoassay capable of detecting secreted materials from individual cells upon activation. If the material of interest is secreted in response to a particular stimulus, then the material will bind to a specific immobilized antibody. Binding is then verified and visualized by applying other antibodies that have been tagged in some way.
Resistance to nearly all known drugs, particularly the most efficacious or non-first line drugs, used in the treatment of a particular disease.
An electrocardiographic finding of a frontal plane QRS axis from -90 to +180 degrees. (CDISC)
A lack of response to the first cycle of therapy.
A lack of response to more than one cycle of therapy.
A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to fetal findings.
A patient's failure to remember to take a dose of medication.

An electrocardiographic finding that occurs when electrical activation of the atria or ventricles occurs from two separate sites. This results in a P wave or QRS complex that displays merged characteristics of beats originating from the two different sites. (CDISC)
A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to digestive system findings.
A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to hematopoietic system findings.

label.value: High Grade Atrioventricular Block by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of intermittent failure of atrial electrical impulse conduction to the ventricles, characterized by two or more consecutive non-conducted P waves. (CDISC)

label.value: High Lateral Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of pathologic Q waves in leads I and aVL, which is suggestive of myocardial infarction of the high lateral wall of the left ventricle. (CDISC)
An individual that has tested positive for pulmonary, laryngeal, or pleural tuberculosis and may or may not present with cavitary disease.
An individual without a stable or permanent residence within the last 365 days.
A way of contracting a disease through interactions with an infected person in the same residence.
The area in which an individual lives.
